HEADWORD: Carpintero
<hw>Car`pin*te"ro</hw> <pr>(k⟦aum⟧r`p⟦esl⟧n*t⟦asl⟧"r⟦osl⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp., a carpenter, a woodpecker.]</ety> <def>A
california woodpecker (<spn>Melanerpes formicivorus)</spn>, noted for
its habit of inserting acorns in holes which it drills in trees. The
acorns become infested by insect larv⟦ae⟧, which, when grown, are
extracted for food by the bird.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Carpodacus</ent>⟦br⟧
